+---
+title: hive setup
+type: command
+source: lib/hive/commands/setup.rb, lib/hive/local_preflight.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [command, setup, local-web, daemon]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: One command for local (non-Docker) product path on Linux/macOS.
+
+## Phases
+
+1. Platform check (Windows → use hivebox)
+2. Dependency matrix (Ruby ≥ 3.4, git, tmux, node/npm, qmd, gh/claude/codex)
+3. Bootstrap Hive-owned: qmd (if npm present), web app provision + bundle
+4. Daemon install/repair to `InvokedBinary` path
+5. Project enrollment when `.hive-state` + global registry match
+6. Managed web service install when systemd-user/launchd available; else print `hive web` + URL
+
+Agent CLIs are **warnings** unless `--strict`. Core blockers: Ruby, web app, daemon binary.
+
+```
+hive setup
+hive setup --json
+hive setup --strict
+```
+
+Related: [[commands/web]], [[commands/doctor]], [[commands/daemon]].
